g to know each other better. <br>
<br>
The officers and leadership want to encourage that growth, and to reinforce the ties between our guild family members. We also want to begin achieving bigger things, now that our seasons and abilities are increasing. In order to meet these goals, we are starting a new chapter in the life of Chivalrous Valor. <br>
<br>
The first change is that we will now be recruiting only new members who are 50+. One of the main problems we have had is that our membership has been too spread out in seasons, so that although we have good numbers, it's been difficult to form family groups and raids. Looking at the guild demographics, nearly all of our members are 40+, so this new recruitment guideline means we will be bringing in folks who will be able to group and fight with our existing members, and will not feel excluded from higher-end guild events. <br>
<br>
That brings me to the second major change for Chivalrous Valor. Being a family means that we care about each other, go out of our way to help each other, and generally have fun together. These are the people you can count on. But that family feeling only gains significance through action. We are asking each of you to put action to our fellowship by committing to attend one guild event per week. What is the point of family if we can't spend time together, help each other with quests and projects, and accomplish greater things together? Your officers and I will be organizing at least 2 guild events per week, at different times, and we ask that you choose one of these events and make sure you attend. <br>
<br>
The events will be varied, including language training, tradeskill farming, quest completion, help with specific targets and drops, work on epics, and raids. All events will be posted on the CV message board, and sign-ups will be requested there. (Although if you don't get a chance to sign up, please don't let that stop you from turning up and attending.) There is also a Raid Requests forum there which you may use to post the projects you are working on. If you don't post your needs there, we won't be able to schedule the events to help you out. We will start small, with events that a group or two can accomplish, and build as we grow. <br>
<br>
Let me be clear, that attendance at at least one guild function per week is *mandatory* for all guild members. If, however, you can't attend the posted events, just have the courtesy to let one of the officers know. A tell in game, an email, or a post on the message board are all acceptable ways to contact us. We have a lot of busy people here, and we will never penalize you for having a Real Life - lol. That being said, we hope the weeks you cannot attend SOMETHING will be few and far between. Please use the Raid Request forum to let us know your scheduling preferences, and we will try to accomodate the majority. <br>
<br>
Again - the change in our levels for recruitment, and the start of mandatory guild events are designed to help us draw together as a family. We will get to know each other better, we will be of more practical help to each other, and we will accomplish exciting things in the coming months. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=18.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm1.threadControl?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub37.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="chi